`` The Sugar Land Express '' also was the nickname of the American football player Kenneth Hall .
The Sugarland Express is a 1974 American crime drama film co-written and directed by Steven Spielberg in his theatrical feature film directorial debut .
It stars Goldie Hawn , Ben Johnson , William Atherton , and Michael Sacks .
It is about a husband and wife trying to outrun the law and was based on a real-life incident .
The event partially took place , the story is partially set , and the movie was partially filmed in Sugar Land , Texas .
Other scenes for the film were filmed in San Antonio , Live Oak , Floresville , Pleasanton , Converse and Del Rio , Texas .
The Sugarland Express marks the first collaboration between Spielberg and composer John Williams .
Williams has scored all but three of Spielberg-directed films since -LRB- Twilight Zone : The Movie , The Color Purple , and Bridge of Spies being the only exceptions -RRB- ; this is the only score he has composed for Spielberg that has never been released as an album , although Williams re-recorded the main theme with Toots Thielemans and the Boston Pops Orchestra for 1991 's The Spielberg/Williams Collaboration .